## Steps

1. [install raspberry pi 5 into argon POLY+ 5 case]
2. [insert microSD card into workstation and download raspberry pi imager from the official raspberry pi website (https://www.raspberrypi.com/software/)]
3. [open raspberry pi imager, select pi model, choose OS (raspberry pi OS lite - 64bit), select correct microsd card to be formatted and imaged with OS]
4. [configure hostname, username and secure password, network credentials, LAN country, time zone, and enable SSH]
5. [write the OS to microSD card]
6. [eject microSD card from workstation, insert into the raspberry pi, and power the device on]
7. [follow the automated setup prompts]  
    - accept the network-wide advertisement blocker setup
    - set static IP via your router admin panel or network application
    - select upstream DNS provider (cloudflare chosen)
    - accept the default block list
    - enable query logging
    - continue through remaining prompts
8. [navigate to router admin panel or network application and set the DNS server to the pihole static ip]
9. [access the pihole admin dashboard at: (private static IP/admin) and login given the default password]
10. [ensure functionality, add additional domain lists as needed, and ensure security by changing default passwords]

